ot only the full scope of the Lettrist project, but also its clear influence on Situationism, the French New Wave, the New Realists, as well as American filmmakers such as Stan Brakhage.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCinematographyzFrancexSpecial effectsxHistoryy20th century. 0aExperimental filmszFrancexHistory and criticismy20th century. 0aLettrism in motion pictures. 0aLettrism. 7aART / General.2bisacsh  agenre films, video, art, french literary criticism, avant-garde movements, postwar paris, lettrism, poetry, painting, fine arts, france, dadaists, surrealists, conceptual artists, 1950s, gil j wolman, maurice lemaitre, francois dufrene, isidore isou, discrepant editing, image, sounds, filming techniques, situationism, american filmmakers, stan brakhage, cinema, film history, eroticism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015z97831106904390 cprintz978022617445740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226174624423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226174624/original  a978-3-11-069043-9  University of Chicago Press Complete eBook-Package 2014-2015c2014d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles